  "texts": [
    "Particularly, given a collective DNN adaptation decision (i.e., a selected set of DNN instances foot_0), Jellyfish first solves the client-DNN mapping problem by applying dynamic programming.",
    "The client-DNN mapping algorithm also leverages batching to the maximum and outputs the corresponding request batching decision for each DNN instance.",
    "Upon system status changes, Jellyfish employs a separate procedure to adapt (select) DNNs incrementally based on simulated annealing (Aarts and Korst 1990).",
    "Finally, Jellyfish keeps informing each client about the input size of the DNN to which they are mapped, so that the client performs data adaptation by sending inference requests with that particular data size.",
    "Jellyfish requires a zoo (collection) of DNN variants with different accuracylatency tradeoff profiles to perform DNN adaptation."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Upon system status changes, Jellyfish employs a separate procedure to adapt (select) DNNs incrementally based on simulated annealing (Aarts and Korst 1990)."
  ]
}